==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Ouch
<hw>Ouch</hw> <pr>(ouch)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OE. <ets>ouch</ets>,
<ets>nouche</ets> (<ets>a nouch</ets> being taken for <ets>an
ouch</ets>: cf. <er>Adder</er>), fr. OF. <ets>nusche</ets>,
<ets>nosche</ets>, <ets>nousche</ets>, buckle, clasp, LL.
<ets>nusca</ets>, fr. OHG. <ets>nusca</ets>, <ets>nuscha</ets>.]</ety>
<def>A socket or bezel holding a precious stone; hence, a jewel or
ornament worn on the person.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>A precious stone in a rich <qex>ouche</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>Sir T.
Elyot.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Your brooches, pearls, and <qex>ouches</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Oughne</ent>⟦br⟧
